{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id784f7283-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s582a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"582a"},"text":"§ 582a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional findings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"It is recognized that research in forestry is the driving force behind progress in developing and utilizing the resources of the Nation’s forest and related rangelands. The production, protection, and utilization of the forest resources depend on strong technological advances and continuing development of the knowledge necessary to increase the efficiency of forestry practices and to extend the benefits that flow from forest and related rangelands. It is recognized that the total forestry research efforts of the several State colleges and universities and of the Federal Government are more fully effective if there is close coordination between such programs, and it is further recognized that forestry schools are especially vital in the training of research workers in forestry. It is also recognized that the provisions of this subchapter are essential to assist in providing the research background that undergirds the Forest and Rangeland Renewable Resources Planning Act of 1974 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1600"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1600","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], the Renewable Resources Extension Act of 1978,"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002456"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002456"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" and the Soil and Water Resources Conservation Act of 1977 ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s2001"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 2001","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id784f7284-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/788/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–788, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/806"},"text":"76 Stat. 806","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/98/tXIV/s1441/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–98, title XIV, § 1441(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1320"},"text":"95 Stat. 1320","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id784f7285-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id784f7286-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id784f7287-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Forest and Rangeland Renewable Resources Planning Act of 1974, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/378"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–378","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-08-17"},"text":"Aug. 17, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/476"},"text":"88 Stat. 476","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to subchapter I (§ 1600 et seq.) of chapter 36 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1600"},"text":"section 1600 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Renewable Resources Extension Act of 1978, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/306"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–306","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/349"},"text":"92 Stat. 349","children":[],"tail":", which was classified generally to subchapter III (§ 1671 et seq.) of chapter 36 of this title, and subsequently was omitted from the Code pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/306/s8"},"text":"section 8 of Pub. L. 95–306","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective and Termination Dates note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1671"},"text":"section 1671 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Soil and Water Resources Conservation Act of 1977, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/192"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–192","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-11-18"},"text":"Nov. 18, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1407"},"text":"91 Stat. 1407","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 40 (§ 2001 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s2001"},"text":"section 2001 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id784f7288-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/98"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–98","children":[],"tail":" inserted provision relating to recognition that provisions of this subchapter are essential to assist in providing the research background that undergirds the Forest and Rangeland Renewable Resources Planning Act of 1974, the Renewable Resources Extension Act of 1978, and the Soil and Water Resources Conservation Act of 1977."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id784f7289-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id784f728a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1981 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/98"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–98","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1981","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/98/s1801"},"text":"section 1801 of Pub. L. 97–98","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s4301"},"text":"section 4301 of Title 7","children":[],"tail":", Agriculture."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id784f728b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/788"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–788","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/806"},"text":"76 Stat. 806","children":[],"tail":", as amended, which is classified generally to this subchapter, is popularly known as the “McIntire-Stennis Act of 1962” and also as the “McIntire-Stennis Cooperative Forestry Act”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id784f728c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Reaffirmation of McIntire-Stennis Research Program","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/624/tXII/s1231"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–624, title XII, § 1231","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-28"},"text":"Nov. 28, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/3543"},"text":"104 Stat. 3543","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/101/624/tXII/s1231"},"text":"“It is the sense of Congress to reaffirm the importance of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/788"},"text":"Public Law 87–788","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s582a"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 582a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) commonly known as the McIntire-Stennis Cooperative Forestry Act.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
